‚Ä¢‚Ä¢ Styling‚Ä¢‚Ä¢
‚Ä¢‚Ä¢The base for a basic form normally contains: <input>, <textarea>, <select>, and <button>.‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢

‚Ä¢‚Ä¢ For fonts it is best to use either "em" or "rem".‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢


‚Ä¢‚Ä¢Increase Font-Size:

.form-element {
  font-size: 1.3rem;
  line-height: 1.2;
} 
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~

‚Ä¢‚Ä¢ Defining our Elements‚Ä¢‚Ä¢
‚Ä¢‚Ä¢ Margin allows us to increase or descrease the space between elements.‚Ä¢‚Ä¢

‚Ä¢‚Ä¢Padding can increase or decrease the space {around} the element.‚Ä¢‚Ä¢

‚Ä¢‚Ä¢We can use CSS to group together elements to help our users identify what should be together.‚Ä¢‚Ä¢


Example:
body {
  font-family: system-ui, sans-serif
}

form div {
  margin-top: 1rem;
}

label,
input,
textarea
button,
select{
  font-size: 1.3rem;
  line-height: 1.2
}

form {
  width: 30em;
  max-width: 90%;
  margin: 0 auto;
}

label {
  margin-bottom: 0.4rem;
  display: block;
}

input,
textarea {
  padding: 0.4rem;
  width: 100%;
}

button {
  margin-top: 2rem;
}
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
‚Ä¢‚Ä¢ When creating forms, it is best to always give it a solid line, to ensure it resemblesba form. Such as using a solid line for <input>:

input,
textarea {
  border: 1px solid;
}
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
‚Ä¢‚Ä¢ Depending on your needs, at times you may want a background for your Buttons:

button {
  margin-top: 2rem;
  background: #3740ff;
  color: #fff;
  border: none;
  padding: 0.6rem;
}

button:hover,
button:focus {
  background: #272eb5
}

~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
‚Ä¢‚Ä¢In this example we will override the default style for :focus: ü¶Ö

button:focus {
    outline: 4px solid green;
}
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~üêõ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
‚Ä¢‚Ä¢When using the <select> tag, this comes with a default styling. We can change and edit this by using the arrow strategy:

select {
    -moz-appearance: none;
    -webkit-appearance: none;
    appearance: none;
    background-color: #fff;
    background-image: url(arrow.png);
    background-repeat: no-repeat;
    background-position: right .7em top 50%, 0 0;
    background-size: .65em auto;
}


‚Ä¢‚Ä¢We can remove the default arrows of a <select>, by using the <appearance> property.‚Ä¢‚Ä¢

‚Ä¢‚Ä¢Now if you wish to show the ‚¨ÜÔ∏è of your choice: We must define the ‚¨ÜÔ∏è as a background.‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
‚Ä¢‚Ä¢Most fonts have a default value of 16px‚Ä¢‚Ä¢

‚Ä¢‚Ä¢Stlying Radio and Checkbox:
First we have to hide the default checkbox and radio button:
input[type="radio"],
input[type="checkbox"] {
   position: absolute;
   opacity: 0;
}

Note: We must use <position: absolute> in combination with <opacity: 0> instead of  using <display: none> & <visibility: hidden> This makes the controls only visually hidden‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢


Now to show our custom elements, we have several options: We can use ::before, the <background> property, or SVG Image:

input[type="radio"] + label::before {
  content: "";
  width: 1em;
  height: 1em;
  border: 1px solid black;
  display: inline-block;
  border-radius: 50%;
  margin-inline-end: 0.5em;
}

input[type="radio"]:checked + label::before {
  background: black;
}
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
‚Ä¢‚Ä¢ Example Styling for CheckBox:

  height: 0.5em;
  border-radius: 50%;
  background: white;
  border: 1px solid white;
  position: absolute;
  left: 0.25em;
  top: 0.25em;
}

input[type="radio"]:checked + label:before {
  background: #3740ff; /* replace with image */
}

input[type="checkbox"]:focus + label:before {
  outline: 2px solid #7AACFE; /* for non-webkit browsers */
  outline: 5px auto -webkit-focus-ring-color;
  outline-offset: 3px;
}

input[type="radio"]:focus + label:before {
  outline: 2px solid #7AACFE; /* for non-webkit browsers */
  outline: 5px auto -webkit-focus-ring-color;
  outline-offset: 3px;
}
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢Example of Accent Color
‚Ä¢‚Ä¢ Basically a one line code to bring your websites styles to a form.

checkbox {
  accent-color: orange;
}
